<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND BOX OFFICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBERT W. WELKOS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 04,38,18,10,10 Weekend Gross/ Screens/ Weeks in Movie (Studio) Total 
(millions) Average Release 1. "Clear and Present Danger" $16 2,433 2 
(Paramount) $55 $6,562 2. "Forrest Gump" $14.1 2,204 6 (Paramount) $188.1 
$6,418 3. "The Mask" $10 2,462 3 (New Line) $70 $4,083 4. "The Little Rascals" 
$7.4 1,925 2 (Universal) $23.3 $3,850 5. "True Lies" $7 2,156 5 (Fox) $112.3 
$3,251 6. "In the Army Now" $6.4 1,444 1 (Hollywood) $6.4 $4,409 7. "The 
Client" $6 2,301 4 (Warner Bros.) $66.5 $2,620 8. "The Lion King" $6 2,221 9 
(Disney) $243.2 $2,706 9. "It Could Happen to You" $4.1 1,544 3 (TriStar) $23.5 
$2,667 10. "Angels in the Outfield" $2.4 1,581 5 (Disney) $41.5 $1,501 * 
"Priscilla, Queen of the Desert" $219,433 7 1 (Grammercy) $295,866 $31,348 Ford 
and Hanks Clearly in Top Form 
</P>
<P>
 The drawing power of Harrison Ford and Tom Hanks was in clear evidence over 
the weekend as two films from Paramount Pictures continued to dominate at the 
box office. Ford's "Clear and Present Danger" brought in $16 million at the box 
office during a weekend in which no big-budget movies debuted. Hanks' "Forrest 
Gump" pulled in more than $14 million in its sixth week of release. To date, 
"Gump" has made more than $188 million.  
</P>
<P>
 The star power of comedian Jim Carrey also worked as New Line Cinema's 
special-effects laden film, "The Mask," grossed $10 million from Friday through 
Sunday, for a three-week total of $70 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Grammercy Pictures' "The Adventures of Priscilla, Queen of the Desert" took 
in a healthy $219,433 on seven screens. 
</P>
<P>
 SOURCE: Exhibitor Relations Co. ROBERT W. WELKOS 
</P>
</TEXT>
