PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NFL; JETS' RECEIVER MOORE HAS BROKEN 
WRIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The New York Jets, already thin at wide receiver, have lost one of their two 
experienced starters, Rob Moore. 
</P>
<P>
 The Jets disclosed that Moore broke his wrist in Saturday's victory over 
Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
 "They told me I have to wait a week and let it calm down," Moore said, 
"They'll take the cast off in 10 days and see what it looks like." 
</P>
<P>
 Former Miami Dolphin safety Louis Oliver, still recovering from a broken foot 
he suffered last November, could miss the first six games for the Cincinnati 
Bengals. Oliver underwent surgery in April to repair the stress fracture. 
</P>
<P>
 Chuck Cecil, a Pro Bowl safety with Green Bay two years ago and a seven-figure 
player last season, was released by the Arizona Cardinals. . . . Kicker Scott 
Sisson was one of seven players cut by the New England Patriots. . . . Wide 
receiver Reggie Rembert was released by Cincinnati along with Patrick Robinson, 
who set a team record last year with 43 punt returns. 
</P>
