<HEADLINE>
<P>
THOUSAND OAKS WINS WORLD SERIES OPENER; LITTLE LEAGUE: STRAUSER, HOWARD TEAM UP 
TO PITCH ONE-HITTER IN 3-0 VICTORY OVER PUERTO RICO. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Strauser and Kevin Howard combined on a one-hitter Monday to spark the 
Thousand Oaks 13-year-old all-stars to a 3-0 victory over defending champion 
Puerto Rico in the opening game of the Little League World Series in Taylor, 
Mich. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks will face Jacksonville (Fla.) in a second-round game of the 
eight-team, double-elimination tournament Wednesday.Jacksonville defeated 
Vestal (N.Y.), 4-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Howard (6-1), who came on in relief with none out and a runner on first in the 
fourth, gave up one hit, struck out six and walked one. 
</P>
<P>
 Strauser did not give up a hit and struck out two, but he walked six. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks (15-1) scored a run in the first, fifth and seventh. 
</P>
<P>
 With one out in the first, Matt Rogers singled and stole second. After Howard 
walked, Wes Munyon singled in Rogers. 
</P>
<P>
 Howard was hit by a pitch with one out in the fifth before moving to third on 
a double by Munyon and scoring on an error by Puerto Rico (9-2). Rogers walked 
to lead off the seventh. Pinch-runner Manuel Apodaca stole second, went to 
third on a wild pitch and scored on a single by Howard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
