<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; PSYCHIC FAIR WILL FEATURE READINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city will have "A Cosmic Affair" this weekend -- a psychic fair offering 
readings by at least a dozen psychic readers and healers from a variety of 
disciplines. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizer Kathy Scott said her fairs are geared for "psychic virgins" and 
veterans and draw an average of 100 to 150 visitors a day. 
</P>
<P>
 "For people who have always wanted to go to a reader it's very good, because 
they can come with a friend and see that there's nothing scary going on," she 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Readings offered will include Tarot cards, palmistry, astrology, psychometry, 
iridology, dream analysis, handwriting analysis, bioenergetic healing and 
"script channeling," in which the spirit guide gives the reader messages 
through her hand. 
</P>
<P>
 Aura photography will be available Sunday only. 
</P>
<P>
 The fair runs from 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. Saturday and Sunday at the Hyatt 
Newporter, 1100 Jamboree Road.  
</P>
<P>
 Admission is $3, with reading prices ranging from $15 to $40, depending on the 
length of the reading. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call Scott at (714) 645-9900. 
</P>
