<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; SCHOOLS MAY ACQUIRE ENERGY-SAVING BUSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Simi Valley Unified School District hopes to receive up to 10 
energy-efficient school buses by participating in a statewide program that is 
demonstrating the new environmentally-friendly vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
 District officials have recommended that the school board pay a consultant 
$3,300 to write a grant proposal to the California Energy Commission to get the 
new buses. 
</P>
<P>
 The board will vote on the expenditure at tonight's meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 The new buses would be a major boost for the school district's transportation 
fleet, which has deteriorated in recent years. 
</P>
<P>
 Last month, the school board approved spending $259,000 to purchase several 
badly needed vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
 In the last year, four school buses, seven maintenance vehicles and a delivery 
truck have been taken out of the fleet because they are beyond repair, a 
district report said. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
