</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The search for the body of a North Hollywood man believed drowned in Lake Piru 
was suspended Monday, after divers and helicopter rescue teams combed the 
waters for nearly 11 hours. 
</P>
<P>
 Amado Carraza, 27, is believed to have drowned in the lake late Sunday 
afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 Carraza left a rented boat at the lake to go for a swim, according to 
Sheriff's Lt. Steve Giles. But shortly after he entered the water, Carraza 
began struggling. 
</P>
<P>
 Members of his family aboard the boat threw him floating devices and at least 
one life vest, but the equipment was no help. 
</P>
<P>
 A relative of Carraza's dove in to try save him but had to let go when the 
struggling swimmer began to pull the other man under the water, Giles said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities believe the accident occurred on the western side of the lake but 
outside of a designated swimming area where water depths range from 15 to 65 
feet. J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
