<LENGTH>
<P>
174 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUPPORT PUBLIC RADIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At KCRW (89.9 FM/Santa Monica; 89.1 FM/Oxnard, Ventura, and 89.3 FM/Indio, 
Palm Springs), our signature station identification says, "National Public 
Radio for more of Southern California." And indeed, since February, 1993, from 
our full-power transmitter in Oxnard and for several years prior via microwave 
and low-power transmitters, KCRW has been providing a wide-ranging menu of 
National Public Radio news, information and cultural programming to Ventura 
County listeners -- many of whom we proudly count among our members. 
</P>
<P>
 While a new public radio station is a reason for any community to celebrate -- 
and we wish KCLU/Thousand Oaks good luck in its endeavor -- we think that your 
readers will be pleased to know that, even though our home base is Santa Monica 
College, KCRU/Oxnard, Ventura (89.1 FM) is on the air 24 hours a day, providing 
the high-quality programs upon which National Public Radio has built its 
award-winning reputation. 
</P>
<P>
 SARAH A. SPITZ 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Monica 
</P>
<P>
 Sarah A. Spitz is director of press relations at KCRW.  
</P>
