<P>
 Hundreds of Haitians taking refuge at the U.S. Navy base at Guantanamo Bay, 
Cuba, rioted Saturday and 65 people -- including 20 U.S. military police -- 
were injured by flying debris, the Pentagon said. Two of the 20 American MPs 
remained hospitalized. The other 18 were treated and released, a Pentagon 
spokesman said. 
