</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ken Griffey Sr. will join the coaching staff of the Bellingham Mariners for 
the remainder of the team's Northwest League season, the Seattle Mariners said. 
</P>
<P>
 Griffey, who has been serving as a roving minor-league hitting instructor, 
will join Bellingham today, Mariner director of player development Jim Beattie 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Griffey was Seattle's hitting coach during the 1993 season. 
</P>
