<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: AMERICAN CYTOGENETICS SEEKS OK TO OFFER SHARES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 American Cytogenetics Inc., a North Hollywood-based operator of cancer 
screening services, has filed an application with the Securities and Exchange 
Commission to offer 4.98 million shares of common stock at about 37 cents a 
share. 
</P>
<P>
 The funds from the sale will be used to finance acquisitions or pay for 
upgrading equipment, said Edward Young, president of American Cytogenetics. 
</P>
<P>
 About 2 million of the shares listed in the application have already been sold 
in private placement, Young said. 
</P>
<P>
 American Cytogenetics reported net income of $16,000 on revenue of $5.28 
million for the year that ended Jan. 31, compared with a net loss of $909,000 
on revenue of $5.7 million the previous year. 
</P>
