<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: BENTON OIL REPORTS 2ND QUARTER PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Benton Oil & Gas Co., an Oxnard-based oil and natural gas exploration and 
production company, reported a second quarter profit after a year-earlier loss. 
</P>
<P>
 The company, which has operations in Louisiana, Venezuela and Russia, reported 
net income of $1.15 million, compared to a loss of $733,860 during the same 
three-month period a year earlier.Revenue in the latest quarter quadrupled to 
$8.48 million from $2 million in the June quarter of 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 For the first six months of 1994, the company reported earnings of $2,000 on 
revenue of $12.2 million, compared to a year-earlier loss of $1.48 million on 
revenue of $3.81 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Benton attributed the second quarter results to stronger performances from its 
domestic and Venezuelan operations. Domestic natural gas sales for the June 
quarter were 478 million cubic feet, which represented a tenfold increase over 
sales a year earlier. Oil sales from the Venezuelan project totaled 614,000 
barrels in the latest quarter, up from 40,000 barrels a year earlier. 
</P>
