<TEXT>
<P>
 Accounting Firms Convert to Limited Liability Partnerships: KPMG Peat Marwick 
and Deloitte & Touche both announced the switch from general partnership to 
protect their partners from personal liability in lawsuits brought against 
their firms.The conversion affects 16,000 Peat Marwick partners and 1,450 
partners at Deloitte & Touche. Without limited liability designation, partners' 
bank accounts and other personal assets could be tapped after the firms 
exhausted all insurance coverage and corporate assets to pay damages in suits 
charging faulty auditing or consulting work, negligence or wrongdoing. Coopers 
& Lybrand and Ernst & Young have also converted to limited liability 
partnerships. 
