$4.5 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Koll Real Estate Group Inc.: The Newport Beach real estate development 
services company said it lost $4.5 million, or 11 cents a share, for the second 
quarter, compared to a loss of $3.5 million, or 9 cents a share, for the like 
period last year. The 1993 quarter included $1.9 million of income from 
discontinued operations.Revenue jumped to $4.8 million from $900,000. The 
company attributed the revenue increase primarily to operations of the domestic 
real estate development business acquired from the Koll Co. in September, 1993, 
as well as sales from a residential project in New Hampshire. For the first 
half, the company had a net loss of $8.5 million, or 20 cents a share. That 
compares with a year-ago net loss of $41.9 million, or $1.05 a share, which 
included a charge of $36 million for an accounting change. Revenue rose to $8.2 
million from $1.1 million. 
</P>
