<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: TRAVEL / TOURISM; DEPARTURE OF RAMS MIGHT BRING ABOUT HILTON 
VACANCIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If the Rams leave Orange County, the Anaheim Hilton may well find itself with 
a few more open rooms. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anaheim Hilton says that it's one of only 13 Hiltons in the chain that are 
officially recognized this season by the National Football League. 
</P>
<P>
 As a result, it is the overnight home to traveling NFL officials, and it 
occasionally hosts NFL teams coming to face the Rams, like the Washington 
Redskins and Detroit Lions last season. 
</P>
<P>
 It has amenities that gridiron stars can appreciate, like the sports and 
fitness center. And, teams that can spare the time from flight schedules might 
like to visit the Rams cheerleaders, who sometimes show up for "Monday Night 
Football" promotions in the bar, according to Hilton staff. 
</P>
</TEXT>
