<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAC RIM SHAREHOLDERS OK CAPITALIZATION DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shareholders of Pac Rim Holding Corp. on Monday approved a previously 
announced deal that will pump $20 million into a wholly owned subsidiary that 
writes workers' compensation insurance in California. 
</P>
<P>
 The cash infusion is being made by PRAC Ltd., an investment partnership 
controlled by Newport Beach investor Richard Pickup. In return, PRAC and Pickup 
will receive convertible debentures and warrants for common stock of Woodland 
Hills-based Pac Rim Holding Corp. 
</P>
</TEXT>
