<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: TRAVEL / TOURISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 'Aladdin' Added: Disneyland has updated one of its oldest -- and most 
simplistic -- rides. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Storybook Land Canal Boats," which small children will instantly 
recognize as the ride in which slow-moving boats are swallowed by Monstro the 
whale, has added scenes from the animated movies "Aladdin" and "The Little 
Mermaid." 
</P>
<P>
 On the ride, which debuted with the opening of the park in 1955, women dressed 
as girls in white knee socks give a guided tour past miniature villages. The 
villages depict scenes from such classic stories as "Cinderella," "The Three 
Little Pigs" and others. 
</P>
<P>
 Now, added to the list are the gold-leafed, onion-shaped domes of the Sultan's 
royal palace from "Aladdin." There is also the marketplace where Aladdin dodged 
the Sultan's guards and met the princess. The lamp? It's in the "Cave of 
Wonders," surrounded by the usual gold booty. 
</P>
<P>
 Also added were Prince Eric's castle from "The Little Mermaid" and the willow 
tree where Ursula the Sea Witch hangs out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
