<P>
 Day Runner Inc.: The Fullerton manufacturer of personal organizers and 
planners recorded a profit of $887,000, or 14 cents a share, for the three 
months ended June 30.Effective Jan. 1, 1994, Day Runner changed its fiscal year 
end from Dec. 31 to June 30. For the comparable quarter last year, the company 
posted a profit of $308,000, or 5 cents a share. Sales rose 89%, to $26.4 
million from $14 million. For the short fiscal year ended June 30, the company 
posted a profit of $2.1 million, or 33 cents a share, on sales of $43.2 
million. That compares with a profit of $1.1 million, or 18 cents a share, for 
the like six months of 1993. 
