</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Davstar Industries Ltd.: The maker of disposable medical products said it 
plans to settle a pending shareholder lawsuit. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the settlement, Davstar will issue warrants to the shareholders allowing 
them to purchase common shares at $5 each through March 20, 1997. The warrants 
will be identical to those that are currently being publicly traded, according 
to the company. 
</P>
<P>
 The number of warrants being issued will have a market value of $1 million, 
based on the trading price of the company's warrants during the 20 days before 
the distribution. The company said it is not admitting any liability through 
the settlement, which is still subject to court approval. 
</P>
</TEXT>
