 Regency Health Services Inc.: The Tustin operator of specialty health care 
facilities posted a second-quarter net loss of $6.5 million, or 40 cents a 
share, which included expenses of $8.3 million from merger and restructuring 
expenses. Regency and Care Enterprises Inc. completed their merger in 
April.That compares with a profit of $2.8 million, or 16 cents a share, for the 
1993 second quarter. Revenue gained 18%, to $96.1 million from $81.5 million. 
