</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More People Flying: Southwest Airlines reports that Orange County is exceeding 
its expectations for passenger growth, and it would like to start additional 
flights at John Wayne Airport. 
</P>
<P>
 In July, the airline boarded 45,572 passengers at John Wayne, a 21% increase 
over 37,727 in June. 
</P>
<P>
 Linda Burke, spokeswoman for Dallas-based Southwest, said the increase is a 
response to the spreading reputation of the airline's low fares. Southwest was 
the first low-fare airline to start service at John Wayne when it began in May 
with 15 daily flights. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is our second full month of service, so we are going to see a learning 
curve as customers see we are convenient and affordable," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
