</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Planning Award: Whether the $3-billion Disneyland Resort expansion project 
goes ahead or not, the planning effort for the project has not gone unnoticed. 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim's planning department has won an award from the Orange County section 
of the American Planning Assn. for its effort to lay out a grand future vision 
of the decayed urban landscape surrounding present-day Disneyland. 
</P>
<P>
 "The project presents a classic, textbook case of utilizing the landscape and 
street-scape," the awards panel noted. "The plan is the highest quality in 
every respect. It sets the standard." 
</P>
<P>
 Planning Director Joel Fick, who accepted the award, said, "This award 
validates our effort to create a world-class resort in the heart of our city." 
</P>
</TEXT>
