<HEADLINE>
<P>
ULTRALINK TO PLAN BENEFITS NETWORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ultralink Inc., a health care network manager, has been selected by Ameritech, 
a telecommunications company in the Midwest, as the planning and network 
manager for Ameritech's health benefits programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Ultralink, in conjunction with the Kennedy Consulting Group in Chicago, will 
develop a network of health maintenance organizations to serve Ameritech's 
employees in five states. Ameritech has 68,000 employees and 50,000 retirees. 
</P>
<P>
 Fees will be linked to an incentive system, said an Ultralink spokeswoman, 
based on when the HMO network begins operations and on how many of Ameritech's 
employees join. 
</P>
<P>
 Ultralink manages more than 200 HMO plans throughout the United States on 
behalf of employers representing more than 120,000 people and more than $150 
million in annualized premiums. 
</P>
</TEXT>
