<HEADLINE>
<P>
GATEWAY REPORTS A LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gateway Communications Inc. reported a net loss of $2.6 million, or 50 cents a 
share, for the second quarter, which included provision of nearly $1.8 million 
for a loss on the sale of substantially all of the company's inventory, 
property, equipment and intellectual property rights to Microdyne Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 Completion of the sale requires the approval of the company's shareholders at 
a special meeting scheduled for Sept. 9.The quarterly loss compares to a loss 
of $586,000, or 12 cents a share, for the 1993 second quarter. Revenue fell to 
$236,000 from $2.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The first-half loss was $3.4 million, or 65 cents a share, compared to a loss 
of $1.1 million, or 21 cents a share, for the comparable six months of 1993. 
Revenue was down to $1.5 million from $5.8 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
