<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: TUSTIN; NEW STUDENT SIGN-UP BEGINS WEDNESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Registration will begin Wednesday for new students who plan to attend schools 
in the Tustin Unified School District in the fall. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration for elementary, middle and high schools will be conducted from 8 
a.m. to 3 p.m. Students are asked to register at their neighborhood school. 
</P>
<P>
 Students entering kindergarten must provide a birth certificate showing that 
they will be 5 years old on or before Dec. 2. Parents also must provide 
immunization records when registering their child. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the school nearest your home or the school 
district's Student Services Department at (714) 730-7325. Classes start Sept. 
8. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
