<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ORANGE; TEMPORARY ASSISTANT SUPERINTENDENT HIRED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Orange Unified School District announced that it has hired a temporary 
assistant superintendent for educational services.Arthur J. Townley, 61, a 
professor of educational administration at Cal State San Bernardino, began 
working in the No. 2 spot on July 14. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's my right-hand person," acting Supt. Robert L. French said. 
</P>
<P>
 Townley, who said he is not applying for a permanent job, supervises physical 
operations and instructional problems at the district's 37 schools. 
</P>
<P>
 He holds a doctorate in education from USC and a master's degree from Cal 
State Los Angeles. He has served as principal, assistant superintendent and 
superintendent of various Southern California schools since 1966. LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</TEXT>
