ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; CABLE TV STATION IN AWARDS CONTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The local cable television station has been nominated for two awards in 
government programming by a national organization of public information 
officers. 
</P>
<P>
 The National Assn. of Telecommunications Officers and Advisors nominated 
Garden Grove Cable Television Corp. for awards in documentary and news series. 
</P>
<P>
 "Girls Club: a Special Report," which profiled the Garden Grove Girls Club, 
was nominated for best documentary, and "This Week in Garden Grove," a weekly 
program about events happening in the city, was nominated for best news series. 
</P>
<P>
 The winners will be announced at a ceremony Sept. 21 in Reno, Nev. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, Garden Grove Cable Television won first place for best news series 
and second place in the special audience category for a piece on disabled 
people.BERT ELJERA 
